title: ISic001784. I.Sicily inscription 001784
body:
Facsimile Images

[---]A ((·)) Valeriu[s? ---]
[---]A ((·)) Fabio ((·)) CE[---]
[---]D ((·)) ( vac. 4) E[---]
[---]us ((·)) esse ((·)) splend[---]
5[---] p̣ṛạẹṣịḍ VC in[---]

Apparatus criticus

Text based on Orsi's drawing; Ce[realis] or Ce[ler] or Ce[nsor]?
5: Upper half of the letters only: PRAESI seems clear; whether D, P or R follows is less clear; VC or VS follows; Orsi's drawing hints at extra space after the first I and before the second I, perhaps suggesting presence of an interpunct.

translation

commentary

The text appears never to have been republished since Orsi 1900, and it has not been seen again.
